					<h4>Literary Odds & Ends</h4>
		
		<h1>Western Book Roundup</h1>
		<h2><i></i></h2>
		<div class="text-feature_print">
							<p>By Jenny Shank, 9-19-07</p>
			
							<table width="25" align="right" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
					<tr>
						<td>&nbsp;</td>
						<td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/thumbnails_feature/one_book_Denver_thumb.gif" align="right" width="176" height="150" /></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/spacer.gif" width="1" height="3" border="0" /></td></tr>

					
					<tr><td><img src="http://www.newwest.net/images/spacer.gif" width="1" height="3" border="0" /></td></tr>
				</table>
			
							<p>Denver Mayor John Hickenlooper announced the official <a target="_blank" href="http://www.denvergov.org/Default.aspx?alias=www.denvergov.org/onebook" title="One Book, One Denver">One Book, One Denver</a> selection Tuesday afternoon: The winner is <i>Articles of War</i>, the debut novel by Denver writer <a target="_blank" href="http://nickarvin.com/" title="Nick Arvin">Nick Arvin</a> which won the Colorado Book Award.&nbsp; Patti Thorn <a target="_blank" href="http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_5701221,00.html" title="reported in the Rocky Mountain News">reported in the Rocky Mountain News</a> about the selection and the program&#8217;s decline in participation.&nbsp; This is the first time a local author will be featured, and Denverites have eight weeks to finish the coming-of-age World War II novel before Arvin&#8217;s reading at Manual High School on November 14.
</p>
<p>
It&#8217;s shaping up to be quite a year for Missoula-based, Colorado-raised fiction writer <a target="_blank" href="http://www.simonsays.com/content/destination.cfm?tab=1&amp;pid=521538" title="Aryn Kyle">Aryn Kyle</a>, whose story &#8220;Allegiance&#8221; was selected by editor <a target="_blank" href="http://www.stephenking.com/" title="Stephen King">Stephen King</a> for the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.houghtonmifflinbooks.com/catalog/titledetail.cfm?textType=toc&amp;titleNumber=689827" title="Best American Short Stories 2007">Best American Short Stories 2007</a>, the annual anthology that is hitting stores soon.&nbsp; Kyle&#8217;s story previously appeared in <a target="_blank" href="http://www.pshares.org/" title="Ploughshares">Ploughshares</a>, and her debut novel, <I>The God of Animals</I>, received a lot of praise when it came out earlier this year (check out my review of it for <a target="_blank" href="http://www.newwest.net/index.php/topic/article/aryn_kyles_ithe_god_of_animals_i/C39/L39/" title="NewWest.Net/books here">NewWest.Net/books here</a>).
</p>
<p>
The American Bookseller&#8217;s Association&#8217;s newsletter <a target="_blank" href="http://news.bookweb.org/booksense/5518.html" title="recently reported">recently reported</a> that <a target="_blank" href="http://kingsenglish.booksense.com/" title="The King's English">The King&#8217;s English</a>, Salt Lake City&#8217;s fine independent bookseller, has been celebrating its 30th anniversary all year long, with sales, author appearances, and redecorating.
</p>
<p>
I recently came across the <a target="_blank" href="http://storytrail.com/SWCL/pages/main.html" title="Southwest Children's Literature website">Southwest Children&#8217;s Literature website</a>, described as &#8220;a collaborative project between undergraduate and graduate students in education, library science, and English and Tucson-area students and their classroom teachers, teacher-librarians, and public librarians.&#8221;  The site features book reviews, author interviews, and reading recommendations with a Southwestern focus for young readers, and breaks out Southwestern books by genre.
</p>
<p>
Have some regional literary news or events to share?&nbsp; If so,  <script type="text/javascript">
